31. By this in briefe may the Invaders

 of Church-Revenues, see the bounds and narrow limits they are included within; There's almost a Noli me tangere to be found cleaving unto them; Sacrum with the Ancients walking by the light of nature only, was as much as Inviolabile;
               Festus.
               Sacro-Sanctum dicebatur quod jurejurando interposito erat institutum, ut qui violasset, morte paenas penderet: Thus Sacro-Sancti Tribuni plebis, sacratissimi Imperatores, among the Romanes; And in this sense doth Cicero Orat. in Catil. 2dâ. use the terme of Sacro-Sanctae possessiones, intimating a kinde of Revenue that was in no wise to be medled with: Pharoah buying all the rest of the Land besides in Aegypt, Exod. 14. 7. yet spares he the Priests possessions there;
